div.p: Step 1: search_tools(brief=true) "What tools exist for web search?"
Returns: name, backend, first sentence, call example ~60 tokens per result
Step 2: tool_info(brief=true) "Tell me more about exa.web_search_exa"
Returns: name, backend, description, parameter names, call example ~200 tokens
Returns: name, description, backend, complete JSON Schema 200 - 10,700 tokens (varies by schema complexity)
Execute the tool via sandbox or direct call
Progressive Discovery (typical) search_tools(brief) 10 results: ~600 tokens tool_info(brief) 1 tool: ~200 tokens tool_info(full) 1 tool: ~2,800 tokens (avg) Total: ~3,600 tokens
Naive: Expose All Tools as MCP 10 tools x ~2,000 tokens each Full schemas sent on every tools/list Total: ~20,000 tokens
@gatemini://tools Load via @-mention in Claude Code Returns ALL tools in compact format ~3,000 tokens for entire catalog
